Today reviewed the results of an Arab youth survey conducted by the international companies Asdaa Pearson-Marsteller and Schwein & Berland.
The poll, which included 16 Arab countries, said that UAE youth are the most optimistic about the future. Positive is part of our identity.
I am pleased that Arab youth are more entrepreneurial, with 67% saying their generation has a greater chance than the previous generation of launching special projects
When Arab youth were asked about the country they prefer to live in, the UAE came first.
When Arab youth were asked about the country that would like your country to follow its example of growth and development, the UAE came first, followed by the United States and France.
I do not remember these results, but we are still at the beginning of the road. I believe that Arab youth have great positive potential that can change the future of the region

The World Organization for Economic Co-operation and Development (OECD) announced the 2013 global aid donor in Paris
With all humility, we say that the UAE has come in first place in the value of official aid for national income worldwide, a news that pleased all of us
Our official aid has increased 375% in 2013 from the previous year .. Our Global Center jumped from the 19th in the world in 2012 to the world's first aid grants in 2013
The United Arab Emirates (UAE) is the world's first humanitarian capital
The tender in the UAE and we inherited from Zayed .. His Knight today is Khalifa bin Zayed and his brothers .. The people of the UAE has never hesitated to support the needy wherever
IMF growth forecast of 2.9% for 2014 is extremely encouraging & proof our #LongTermEconomicPlan is working, providing security for people.
Brussels is becoming a global diplomatic hub - like Vienna! In June we'll welcome G7 leaders in our premises in Brussels.
Last #EUCO decided to deepen energy union & reducing EU dependency on Russian gas.
EU will continue to strengthen our ties with #Georgia and #Moldova; signature of full Association Agreements brought forward to June.
Together, we Europeans provide more than half of the world’s development and humanitarian aid.
EU has 7,000 men & women currently involved in 16 civilian & military missions & operations, on 3 continents. Mission #CAR just launched
Europe is an economic player; together, our countries are the world's 1st economy, bigger than US or than China & India combined.
Today the 2013 donor countries worldwide have been announced by the OECD in Paris.
We are humble and pleased that the UAE came in the 1st place worldwide in terms of the value of its official aids as a percent of GNI
Our official aids increased by% 375 in 2013 compared to 2012 making a leap from the 19th place to the 1st place worldwide.
According to the OECD, the UAE's aids exceeded $ 5bn in 2013 making it the number one humanitarian capital worldwide.
The culture of giving is deeply rooted in our society, and it has been always nurtured by UAE leaders since theception of the UAE
